                            <comment id="13272002" author="ggezer" created="Thu, 10 May 2012 00:59:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;There is a little bug in IPojoFactory.stop() method,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;        m_state = INVALID; // Set here to avoid to create instances during the stops.&lt;br/&gt;
        ............................&lt;br/&gt;
        ...........................&lt;br/&gt;
        if (m_state == VALID) {&lt;br/&gt;
            for (int i = 0; i &amp;lt; m_listeners.size(); i++) &lt;/p&gt;
{
                ((FactoryStateListener) m_listeners.get(i)).stateChanged(this, INVALID);
            }
&lt;p&gt;        }&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;m_state if changed to INVALID before the check for state notifications.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13284312" author="clement.escoffier" created="Mon, 28 May 2012 07:35:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Was fixed in trunk. Waiting for confirmation.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13284494" author="ggezer" created="Mon, 28 May 2012 17:42:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s fixed. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
